criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  clinical CHD (such as angina pectoris, myocardial infarction) diagnosed by dynamic
             electrocardiogram and ultrasonic cardiogram;

          -  coronary atherosclerosis confirmed by coronary angiographic examination;

          -  cerebral infarction diagnosed by cerebral CT;

          -  common carotid artery intimal-media thickness (IMT) ≥1.2 mm measured by Doppler
             ultrasonic examination;

          -  extensive irregular stenosis of a lower extremity artery (diameter < 3mm) or
             segmentally obstructed.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  age ＜ 20 years

          -  age ＞ 60 years
